<subSubSection id="AF873BCBEA5CB5A345EB2D98D8FBA38F" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="5B4EF86D753131C8E0656D8A99007D04" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">
<taxonomicName id="DAFABB53562E0DAD290DF000E6152116" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Evarthrus</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1853a: 226, 227. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="6AA3FD80C83F8945CB62EF10817DB9DD" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1823" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sigillata">
<emphasis id="F4E6396A47CF3E51FC7BF843B243380F" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">Feronia sigillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Say, 1823 designated by Casey (1918: 322). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="81E18D321AB58CF3FF4EC658DAB05834" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">ev</emphasis>
(original, primitive, by extension simple) and 
<emphasis id="F9748C1AB8F354EFB731BBB8BE899CE8" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">arthron</emphasis>
(joint), possibly alluding to the simple (i.e., non carinate) basal antennomeres (&quot; 
<emphasis id="ABEE26EB80AA0807824B91BD29D449B9" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">antennae articulis basalibus simplicibus</emphasis>
&quot;) of the adult [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D6EF72CDEC696D740497377C3A3341B" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">
<taxonomicName id="76AB1FA0B8E29303959EF8F3F992EC9C" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anaferonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Anaferonia</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 341. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="DE758368410E03280AF3146414C67D01" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1823" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constricta">
<emphasis id="FB5A98B4DB658074737E2E94F6CFFEF8" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">Feronia constricta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Say, 1823 by original designation. Synonymy established by Freitag (1969: 126). Etymology. From the Greek prefix 
<emphasis id="7300E0889EEC457B22F1C5DC9E99D3EB" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">ana</emphasis>
- (up, back, again) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="0CE79D675241F522C80EB4CCD8665534" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Feronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1C4C39453E07D3FA31785DB602BEA0A4" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">Feronia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="D7AADAB3AC203496DC2A4E11709C066E" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">q.v</emphasis>
.] [feminine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1295F846D99D72BE345F1D2E0527A657" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">
<taxonomicName id="CF6DCFEE881E4AD2CB5E5853F9A54511" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Megasteropus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Megasteropus</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 350. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="C2BD45E861CFC938D2942444CF63E5C1" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Megasteropus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas">
<emphasis id="7A5416D140330AB34A1731300D76AF2F" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">Megasteropus gigas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918 by original designation. Synonymy established by Freitag (1969: 126). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="8F809A179DFA60B2356288E71E117987" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">megas</emphasis>
(large) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="804D6E77489EB453DF81284FBDB87656" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Steropus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A2F5D2F4094B34D4538A2FB502B9C7FF" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">Steropus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5795DF2E47D477D3E7933A936ED64B71" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">
<taxonomicName id="3A1FA1B66096B90294A03AB75D78B77F" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Eumolops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eumolops</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 351. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="3D5D344D0B597E381577C8A4C4526B31" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Eumolops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sexualis">
<emphasis id="9D362584D55F9DF8503922F3870BECDB" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">Eumolops sexualis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918 (= 
<taxonomicName id="51CB1AF0EBBD25138DACED2CF74425D5" authority="torvus" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="torvus" subSpecies="torvus">
<emphasis id="C87FE289FBBAD7E50817160E88844320" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">Evarthrus torvus torvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1863) by original designation. Synonymy established by Freitag (1969: 127). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="762485E9985D22390D023B33D0EB895D" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">eu</emphasis>
(agreeable, primitive) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="70E1FB9F6DDB2D7FBC713DAD5AEB2318" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Molops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4466E53FA973603A27F94FBC7EBEC796" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">Molops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="17C9BEB398B2FB1A3917E75D2A790A71" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">
<taxonomicName id="5683E1D7F5F763F3DB265A99A191C781" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Evarthrinus</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918: 357. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="C4EB408425612A1E2124D7B76B9F40C7" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Eumolops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decepta">
<emphasis id="500EBEBCD2F6E5713A6C4C64B4AB05E9" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">Eumolops decepta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1918 designated by Freitag (1969: 127). Synonymy established by Freitag (1969: 127). Etymology. From the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="181C97B3D212B73CE2E0082C3FB7EC83" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="433DBD1351F580370D7F1D97E5A73540" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">Evarthrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="97351F41DDA728CD412D3DCF18DCCD51" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">q.v</emphasis>
.] and the Latin suffix - 
<emphasis id="02495983AD4D2284B0BA4431826D6A35" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">inus</emphasis>
(pertaining to) [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="561F5457DE813F9051A6EF01443F6EF3" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">
<taxonomicName id="86EC24E0024A823B05BB78C47F4024D7" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1920" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Evarthrops</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1920: 194. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="21D955E8AA7839985E933441DD76A481" baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furtivus">
<emphasis id="4264F3E164C926B01C260FC5E30E82F7" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">Evarthrus furtivus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1853 designated by Freitag (1969: 127). Synonymy established by Freitag (1969: 127). Etymology. From the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="235CC107E872D28751E154F441D9D525" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Evarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="554" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5328B502F612F669FF80004B6500CCB7" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">Evarthrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="8242B2D0F1DEE387625CF3C802D6003A" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">q.v</emphasis>
.] and the Greek suffix - 
<emphasis id="8A57ADCB1A8E003782B8BE9F1E5AAF59" italics="true" pageId="554" pageNumber="555">ops</emphasis>
(having the appearance of) [masculine].
</paragraph>
